About this hotel

A 7-minute walk from Collblanc metro station, this informal spa hotel is 13 minutes' walk from Camp Nou stadium, home of the Barcelona football club, and 7 km from Gaudi's renowned Sagrada Família.

Check-in time: 2:00 PM
Check-out time: 12:00 PM

    4/5
    A three night mini break in October, costing about £500 for room only (Executive double). The hotel is very convenient from the airport (Metro L9 sud) and situated in a quiet non-touristy area. Pretty good for the centre too using Metro L5. …
    A three night mini break in October, costing about £500 for room only (Executive double). The hotel is very convenient from the airport (Metro L9 sud) and situated in a quiet non-touristy area. Pretty good for the centre too using Metro L5. Don't bother paying for breakfast - plenty of great cafes and bars just across the road that cost a fraction of the price.
    The good bits : the roof top terrace and pool is nice with quite a few loungers. The spa (19 euro for guests) in the basement is fantastic! One of the best. Several different pools of various types and temperatures, two large saunas and a steam room. The room was a nice size with a large window to open. Bed was massive and very comfortable.
    However there were a few issues. The air con seemed to stop working on day one and the bathroom would often smell very unpleasant like drains. We kept the door shut and this made it bearable.
    The staff on the front desk were extremely polite and helpful.

    Stayed here peak season with my 2 kids 9 & 6 at short notice. Was attracted by the pool, spa and 5 min walk to metro which takes to direct to Sagrada Familia- 15 min away. Very safe residential area. The staff were so friendly and kind. The …
    Stayed here peak season with my 2 kids 9 & 6 at short notice. Was attracted by the pool, spa and 5 min walk to metro which takes to direct to Sagrada Familia- 15 min away. Very safe residential area. The staff were so friendly and kind. The breakfast wasn’t included but was good - 12e for adults and 6e for kids. The swimming pool is only open till 9pm and very small- 5m x 3m approx. The spa is actually 6-7 thermal pools and a sauna / Hammam / ice room which was 10e extra for kids and 20e extra for adults. We found it pricey but the kids loved it - they have never been allowed in other places. It’s only open for kids between 10-12pm. Menu was ok too - fresh food options such as make your own salad and steak was good. Bar staff really kind. Abit tired and pricey, but overall a good stay which met our needs! Also 5 min walk to Camp Nou for football fans and 10 min taxi to Caixa Cosmos - possibly the best science museum ever with an Amazon rainforest & planetarium. Would give this 4 star if it had abit of a refurb which could be easily achieved with a refresh of artwork!

    Em Holmes6 months ago on Google
    3/5
    This hotel looks like it was great at one point in time, but it looks very tired now. The letters have all fallen off on the sign on both the building and the driveway entrance. The fountains inside aren't running water. The check in line …
    This hotel looks like it was great at one point in time, but it looks very tired now. The letters have all fallen off on the sign on both the building and the driveway entrance. The fountains inside aren't running water. The check in line was long with only one person working. The taxis take a long time to come to this location. However, the lobby area looks pretty and all the staff were very polite and nice. The hallways and room were clean.
    The bed was decent, but not the typical comfortable hotel bed you're used to. The room was nice, but the chair inside looked very old and was covered in stains. The soap dispensers in the bathroom and shower were empty, but the staff came promptly to fix it.
    The rooftop pool is very peaceful, but the door was broken and we had to wait for maintenance to get it open for us.
    The spa area was very relaxing. 19€ for 1.5 hours inside, which was plenty of time. There are many different pools, but it is not clear what benefits each one provides. The water was room temperature, and it could have been warmer for better relaxation. I think the most helpful were the sauna, quiet room, and neck jets. Everything else felt more for show (lemons and rocks in a pool? Not sure those make a difference). Still, it's a neat concept and design, just didn't feel like it provided as much value as one would think - but for the price, it's not bad.
    The hotel is 5 min walking from the metro into the city, it was easy to figure out. Walking distance to plenty of restaurants.

    About this hotel

    A 7-minute walk from Collblanc metro station, this informal spa hotel is 13 minutes' walk from Camp Nou stadium, home of the Barcelona football club, and 7 km from Gaudi's renowned Sagrada Família.…

    The relaxed rooms offer free Wi-Fi, flat-screen TVs, and tea and coffeemaking facilities; upgraded rooms add pull-out sofas. Room service is available.

    There's a casual buffet restaurant with live cooking stations, a piano bar, and an airy lobby with seating; breakfast is available for a surcharge. A spa offers whirlpool tubs and saunas, plus treatment rooms and a gym. Other amenities include a seasonal rooftop pool and a sundeck.
